rest_of_day_open: I think it's going to be a good week. I have a couple days off work due COVID, and that means I get to spend more time with my family. Work is going to be a bit difficult when I go back, but I'll manage. I think overall it's going to end up boding semi-decent.
critical_positive: I think what worked well is the fact that we were both laid back and easy going. I think the fact that we had similar aged children certainly helped make the conversation flow better as well. Lastly I think our similar views in regards to the coronavirus and how people are handing it helped make things work well.
critical_negative: I don't think there was much that didn't work well. I think there was a slight language barrier, so that might have made things a bit difficult. I think my partner had a hard time understanding me as well due to the language barrier and my voice was probably pretty muffled.

rest_of_day_open: I am thinking very positively about my coming week. I am pretty much-staying stong safe to protect my family. I will support my kids and my husband with full energy. Since living with this pandemic is exhausting, I believe that in the coming days we would definitely find a solution and we can hope for the best.
critical_positive: I felt that my conversation partner is a very polite person. Even though he was polite he was also very friendly so I was comfortable talking with him. We both had similar thoughts and we feel the same way to protect our family and friends. While talking I felt that he is a simple and good father to his kids.
critical_negative: Our interaction went very smoothly but at some places, I felt that it might stop. So I tried very hard to keep the conversation going. I was also a little bit worried that I might bore him with my stories and my opinion. My conversation partner did not ask many questions but he answered all my questions.
